Additional EUR 400 million for infrastructure
János Veres, Minister of Hungarian Finance, and Marta Gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB), signed, Friday, Budapest, three agreements of a total value of EUR 400 million on a credit line to support education, transport and environment infrastructure and energy.
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) adopted a budget of EUR 300 million for the Hungarian budget financing of transport and environmental projects to be carried out from the Cohesion Fund whose credit contract worth EUR 100 million has already been signed by the parties, and this time the signed contract concerns the use of the remaining EUR 200 million.
The EUR 150 million loan agreement also covers the budgetary financing of educational projects.
The EIB has approved a total of EUR 300 million for Hungary, and the remaining EUR 150 million can be used later, following the extension of the credit agreement.
The parties signed a EUR 50 million contract for innovation, the state budget will use this envelope in the first place as part of the research and development project to be carried out at the University of Debrecen.
In the negotiations, the draft metro line 4 was also discussed.
The parties agreed that they would reconsider the possible modification of the initial contract when Hungary has finalised the details of the financing of the metro with the EU.
According to János Veres, this could be done in the first quarter of 2008.
Since 1990, the EIB has granted a total of EUR 8.4 billion to finance 113 projects in Hungary.
The EIB grants its appropriations according to the interest rate linked to EURIBOR, with a grace period of 8 years and without a commitment commission.
Bulgaria, a paradise of the EU real estate market
The evolution of the Bulgarian real estate market is spectacular, the attention of the whole of Europe is turned to this Balkan country, which has not been mentioned in the past.
What, or who buys in this EU market that is always the cheapest but which will quickly become expensive?
Analysis of the Bulgarian division of Re/Max.
Currently, in the real estate, Bulgaria is unquestionably the most in vogue target in Eastern Europe with its ski apartments and houses on the cheap seashore.
In the mountains, the most popular regions are Bansko, Borovec, Pamprovo and Vitosa and, on the seashore, Albena, the \"Sables of gold\" the \"Côte du sole\" the former Sozopol and Nessebar but they are increasingly looking for a building in the Kavarna and Balcik area as well.
According to the analysts of Re/Max Bulgaria, sooner or later, the central region of the country, namely Veliko Tarnovo, Gabrovo, Elena, Triavna, will also awaken the interest of investors and they are also increasingly to buy in the cheap corner of Ruse.
Sofia, the capital, also offers attractive opportunities, trade and office areas promise the highest amortization rate.
Bulgaria is on the best track to become one of Europe's most attractive golf paradises and thus be a priority destination, after the summer season and winter season, also in the other two seasons of the year.
More vigilant investors already buy in large numbers, for example in Bansko's corner.
According to analysts, people buying a building in Bulgaria also seek to change their lives, their way of life.
Most buyers are English but others come from France, Belgium, Spain and more and more from Romania.
Maltese and Cypriot investors are also present. On the shores of the Black Sea and in the most famous ski resorts, we traditionally meet many Russian buyers.
Foreign buyers are divided into three groups, said Georgij Jankov, Regional Director of Re/Max Bulgaria.
People who intend to settle buy renovated buildings, at a price ranging from 50 to 100 thousand euros, or old damaged houses, at a price ranging from 5 to 15 thousand euros, which are then renovated.
The criteria are easy access and communication opportunities, the proximity of a large city, shops and in general that of the local doctor.
The second group includes buyers of secondary residences (since December, Bulgaria has been listed among the first 10 holiday destinations in Germany).
The third group is made up of commercial investors who buy in the hope of achieving a medium- or long-term surplus value.
The price of capital buildings is increasing steadily due to an ever-increasing demand.
In the European Union, real estate prices are the lowest in Bulgaria. However, in the last 5 years, they have increased by 21 per cent each year.
The increase in real estate prices mainly exceeds the increase in wages.
Fodor and the six percent Hungarian
According to the communication by Gábor Fodor, Minister of Environment and Water, professional meetings are completed on Tuesday, but Wednesday, after official opening, the negotiations of Ministers on the international climate regime after 2012 will continue.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries around the world will discuss the Bali Roadmap to define the efforts to be made after the emission reduction period defined by the Kyoto Protocol until 2012.
At this time, intensive discussions are being held between developing and developed countries on this issue.
The United States also reported that, for the time being, they did not want to discuss accurate figures, but that they were ready to sign an agreement on the reduction of greenhouse gas emissions from 25 to 40 per cent compared to the 1990 level.
Another important issue of the conference is whether developed countries undertake, without reducing emissions, to provide financial and technological assistance to countries in need.
An agreement was also signed on aid to developing countries.
The aid fund defined by the Kyoto Protocol will be managed by an Executive Board of 16 members, probably within the framework of the UN Global Environment Fund (GEF), which announced Piac es Profit (Market and Profit).
Six percent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, Gábor Fodor, Minister of the Environment and Waters, confirms the EU's ambition to maintain its admiral vessel role in global efforts to protect the climate and to encourage the signing of the new international agreement before 2009.
The Minister explained that the EU was committed to reducing its greenhouse gas emissions by 20 per cent by 2020 compared to the 1990 level, regardless of the success of signing the \"After 2012 Agreement\", and was prepared to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by up to 30 per cent if the other major regions of the world and/or developing countries were also ready to make commitments appropriate to their responsibility and capacity.
Gábor Fodor recalled that in 1997, the Kyoto Protocol's signatory countries totalled 5.2 per cent, and all 15 EU members at that time made a commitment of 8 per cent less.
Hungary has made a commitment to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 6 percent compared to the period between 1985 and 1987, our country will fulfil its commitment, recalls the press release of the Ministry of the Environment.
The issue is great in Bali because the long-term international agreement on climate policy should be put in place in the two-year period, otherwise the entry into force of the agreement would certainly be postponed after 2012. In this case, the commitments to reduce below the values provided for in the Kyoto Protocol would not be followed immediately by a new international emission reduction system, which was highlighted in the new IPCC report, an international scientific body, which was awarded the United Nations Nobel Peace Prize to deal with climate change.
The reduction in emissions would be delayed and the increase in the average temperature of the Earth to more than 2 degrees celcius could no longer be avoided which, according to scientists, would have extremely serious and irrevocable consequences.
British Army Recruits YouTube · Global Voices
British Army units provide video-sharing sites with records made during their operations in Iraq and Afghanistan with a view to popularizing.
First, it was the British Air Force (RAF) that was passionate about YouTube: the special units intervening in Afghanistan were charging video sequences on Taliban operations since March 2006, announced the BBC.
These recordings, taken using mini-camera cameras mounted on the helmet, are controlled at the headquarters of air force operations in Kandahar and are then transferred to Londrès or the compatriots charge them on the Internet.
The political message is indisputable
Air Force soldiers have already spent 139 sequences on the net by this route and their \"chain\" was watched by more than 75,000 people.
The British Ministry of Defence registered itself as \"defenceheadquarters\" in spring 2007 and reports videos on operations in Iraq and Afghanistan while the Commonwealth Department (Commonwealth Office) and the international peacekeeping forces in Iraq (MNFI) also have their own channels on YouTube.
Mission to Afghanistan
According to the initial objective of the air force, the videos were passed on the net to recruit. According to the Ministry of Defence, they were also used to publicize the real objectives of the presence of the army abroad.
The propaganda published in this way costs virtually nothing in relation to the usual recruitment advertisements passed on to television, communicated to BBC Gordon Mackenzie, consulting in defence, but it also inevitably carries a political message as it warrants in a special form the well-founded military operations decided by the government.
The Americans made a game
The army is ambushed because, apart from the videos composed and carefully censored, amateur videos have passed on the sharing site that also present, for example, the death of soldiers: in the \"official\" propaganda films, a little hypocritical, officers do not avoid talking about losses but never present the bloody side of the fight.
In fact, many videos had already been made on the net showing the areas of operations in Iraq and Afghanistan that were being carried out on a real mission, but the British army had been packing for the loading of these videos only recently.
The Americans are recruiting a little differently by using the American's Army rifle game downloadable for free. In this game the player can put himself directly in place of the soldiers in a more or less real simulation.
