This means that the date of the end of the strike, from the day of the vote in parliament on the Health Insurance Act, is not defined.
If the National Assembly does not adopt the Health Insurance Act, the unions will withdraw the strike call immediately.
On the other hand, if the law is voted, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the follow-up to be taken.
