The National Association of Physicians will strike across the country in alternation, the Health and Social Sector Employees Union (EDDSZ) attached to the SZEF will make a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League requires the Government to withdraw its proposal on health reform and to submit a new concept to the social debate.
The second claim requires that the new method of calculating the pension to be established from next year be introduced in several stages.
The third claim is a guarantee, in terms of retirement before the legal age, which would allow the system to pass on the functions it deserves before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is the rejection by the Roadpath Free Union (VDSZSZ), linked to the League Unions, the proposal of the Ministry of Economics and Transport concerning secondary rail lines and the expectation of another proposal.
Political Capital: the Hungarian Guard has increased the risk of countries
According to the Political Capital Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, established last August, with the support of Jobbik Magyarországért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary) increases, in several respects, the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In its \"risk warning\", the society reports that, in relation to the Hungarian Guard's activity, the greatest political risk is already that \"in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur following the worsening ethnic tension existing between the Tzygan and non-Tzygan population of Hungary\".
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's policy strategy, which is likely to lead to this situation, is the main reason.
As they say, this is one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: \"public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groupings that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Tzygans and the Hungarians.\"
The problem is aggravated, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are strengthened and aggressive conflicts are more likely to occur, they say.
However, according to the research institute, the work of the Hungarian and international media \"has significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, in particular with regard to confidence in the country's stability and democratic maturity.\"
They recall that, following greater publicity given to the reorganization of the Hungarian radical and extreme right groups since the fall of 2006, many associations have been formed in Hungary since the summer of 2007, calling themselves the \"national self-defense association\".
\"The common feature of these gatherings is that they define themselves as a civil organization when they publicly declare the preparation of their adherents to defence missions (catastrophes, national defence, defence of order), armed if necessary, further, referring to the ineptitude of the police, the army, in other words the state,\" they added.
They pointed out that everything was in line with the method, which, based on the spite of the political society and the parties, seeks to disguise different political ambitions from a civil point of view.
