On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
- Bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year it may allow itself to increase the bonuses - clarified Noguera.
Over the age of 25 this becomes easier for drivers when entering into a contract with insurance, as the rate of claims is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is preferable to choose a risk insurance with freeness of choice.
\"Youths generally cannot benefit from the prior experience acquired after an accident,\" says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet it is preferable for him to negotiate insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the lowest in the accident rate, because increases will be lower.
